1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,002
Sir, I don't think Reyes is involved.

2
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:05,922
[Jalil] <i>He's also trying to find out</i>
<i>what happened on the island.</i>

3
00:00:06,005 --> 00:00:08,341
<i>I've suspected for a long time</i>
<i>that he was up to something.</i>

4
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:10,468
<i>That's why I don't think</i>
<i>he knows anything.</i>

5
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:11,553
What about the people with him?

6
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:13,096
[Jalil] <i>I'm still investigating them.</i>

7
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:16,683
[Manuel] <i>What are you doing</i>
<i>in front of my house?</i>

8
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:18,852
[in English] <i>Are you spying on me?</i>

9
00:00:19,394 --> 00:00:21,521
[Lara] <i>Why did you follow me</i>
<i>all the way to my dad's house?</i>

10
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:23,523
[Jalil] <i>I'm just trying to find out</i>
<i>what you're hiding.</i>

11
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:25,525
[Lara, in English]
<i>Are you interrogating me?</i>

12
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:26,401
We'll get there eventually.

13
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:30,321
[Marcus] <i>He developed</i>
<i>post-traumatic stress disorder.</i>

14
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:33,783
[Ramli] <i>I owed him a great debt,</i>
<i>so I immediately hid him.</i>

15
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,994
[Marcus] <i>I'm not leaving this place until</i>

16
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:37,370
<i>I find out what really happened.</i>

17
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,205
[Ramli] <i>That's proof</i>
<i>that Datu Rahman is innocent.</i>

18
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:40,915
[Ramli] <i>He allegedly refused</i>
<i>to hand it over to the authorities</i>

19
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:42,625
<i>because he didn't know</i>
<i>which members of the police</i>

20
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:44,294
<i>were protecting the syndicates.</i>

21
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:46,755
[man] <i>We followed the Muslim man,</i>
<i>Usman Sabdani.</i>

22
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:48,423
<i>He was meeting with Marcus Reyes,</i>

23
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:50,675
<i>and they were going to an abandoned place.</i>

24
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:52,343
- <i>It looks like they're hiding something.</i>
- [Lara] <i>Datu Rahman.</i>

25
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:53,928
[Datu Rahman] <i>What do you want from me?!</i>

26
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:55,096
- [Datu Rahman grunting]
- [blow lands]

27
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,639
[man] <i>Don't make any trouble!</i>

28
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:59,184
[Marcus] <i>I'll fix</i>
<i>whatever needs to be fixed.</i>

29
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:03,563
<i>I'll make sure I find out</i>
<i>who's behind all of this.</i>

30
00:01:03,646 --> 00:01:05,440
[man] <i>You're confiscating our belongings?</i>

31
00:01:05,523 --> 00:01:06,775
<i>You think you'll succeed?</i>

32
00:01:06,858 --> 00:01:08,902
<i>One of our accomplices</i>
<i>is from your side too.</i>

33
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:10,904
<i>High-ranking officials in the NLEA.</i>

34
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:14,199
<i>So no matter how many times</i>
<i>these weapons are confiscated,</i>

35
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:15,742
<i>they'll just find their way back to us.</i>

36
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:18,369
[suspenseful music playing]

37
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:21,206
- [man 1] <i>What's happening?</i>
- [man 2] <i>Check the breaker!</i>

38
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,798
Check on them!

39
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:33,092
- [blows landing]
- [man grunting]

40
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:39,349
[mysterious theme music playing]

41
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,322
[suspenseful music playing]

42
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:24,394
- [thuds]
- [Jalil grunts]

43
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:26,229
[man groans]

44
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:29,149
[suspenseful music continues]

45
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:35,405
[Jalil groans]

46
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,414
[man shouts angrily]

47
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:47,709
- [man shouting angrily]
- [Jalil groaning]

48
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:50,837
[shouts angrily]

49
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:51,880
- [blow lands]
- [Jalil grunts]

50
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,466
[man groans]

51
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:58,011
[man shouts, grunts angrily]

52
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:02,140
- [Jalil grunts]
- [man groans, shouts]

53
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:09,022
- [man shouting]
- [suspenseful music continues]

54
00:03:09,105 --> 00:03:15,862
- [Jalil grunting, groaning]
- [man shouting]

55
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:20,491
[man grunts]

56
00:03:24,787 --> 00:03:25,997
[man shouts]

57
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:29,208
[shouting]

58
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:32,921
‪[man shouts]

59
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:34,839
[shouts]

60
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:37,759
[shouts]

61
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:38,885
[man grunts]

62
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:40,929
Stay on guard here!

63
00:03:41,846 --> 00:03:44,390
[tense music playing]

64
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:11,459
- [Jalil breathes heavily]
- [music intensifies]

65
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,134
‪[Jalil grunts]

66
00:04:26,891 --> 00:04:28,309
[man groans]

67
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:50,164
[tense music continues]

68
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:57,797
We're screwed!

69
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:11,144
- [line ringing]
- Hello!

70
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,146
Hello!

71
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,898
Ma'am, we're under attack here!

72
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:17,108
What?

73
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:22,322
[tense music playing]

74
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:27,869
He can't escape!
Don't let them take Datu Rahman.

75
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:29,454
- [thwacks]
- [man 2 grunts]

76
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:31,080
[man 2 grunting, groaning]

77
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:33,791
Hello? Hello!

78
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,626
- [kick lands]
- [Jalil grunts]

79
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,590
Hello! What's happening there?! Answer me!

80
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:43,092
- [thwacks]
- [man 2 grunting]

81
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:49,265
- [music intensifies]
- [Jalil gasping]

82
00:05:49,348 --> 00:05:50,558
[Lara on the phone] <i>Hello!</i>

83
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:53,227
<i>What's happening there?!</i>

84
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:09,262
[tense music continues]

85
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,233
[in Arabic] <i>Allah is sufficient for us…</i>

86
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:29,031
<i>and He is the best Disposer of affairs.</i>

87
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:31,868
[rapid gunfire]

88
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:10,490
What are you doing here--

89
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:11,991
Don't come any closer!

90
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:16,579
‪[dramatic sting]

91
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,665
- [Jalil] Father!
- Jalil?

92
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,918
[Datu Rahman] Son?

93
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:28,758
- How did you get here?!
- Father!

94
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:32,094
Father, we have to go.
I'll explain everything later.

95
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,054
[Jalil breathes heavily]

96
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:36,140
[Jalil] We have to go. [grunts softly]

97
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:39,560
Come on.

98
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:43,147
[tense dramatic music playing]

99
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:50,863
[Jalil breathing deeply]

100
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:52,323
[Jalil] Father…

101
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:55,201
- Can you fight?
- Just like before, son!

102
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:58,287
- Just like before.
- Just like before.

103
00:09:00,289 --> 00:09:01,165
‪[heavy breathing]

104
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:13,594
What happened here? Who did this?

105
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:16,180
Chief will kill us!

106
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:18,099
[tense music continues]

107
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:28,317
[Marcus] <i>You're the ones</i>
<i>ruining the police's reputation.</i>

108
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:33,322
<i>I'll make you pay for all your sins.</i>

109
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:48,296
[gunshots]

110
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:50,131
‪[body thuds]

111
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:51,799
‪[mysterious music playing]

112
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:54,802
‪[dramatic sting]

113
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:58,389
‪[dramatic sting]

114
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,474
‪[dramatic sting]

115
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,982
[crickets chirping]

116
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:09,859
[music intensifies]

117
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:20,911
[line ringing]

118
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:27,710
[phone buzzing]

119
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,089
- Brother…
- [Marcus] <i>Brother.</i>

120
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:35,343
I'm on my way back to Manila.

121
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:36,552
Brother, there's a problem.

122
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:38,304
What?

123
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:39,347
Datu Rahman…

124
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,350
They took Datu Rahman.

125
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:44,143
What?!

126
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:48,022
Brother, I'm sorry. There were armed men

127
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:49,565
who took Datu Rahman from the safe house.

128
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:52,109
I'm looking for them now.

129
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,445
But I don't even know where to look.

130
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,949
[stirring music playing]

131
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:05,873
[sighs] Alright, brother,
try to find them.

132
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:08,334
[sharp inhale] I'm on my way back.

133
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:09,877
[breathes heavily]

134
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,463
- Update me.
- Of course, brother.

135
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:14,131
[car horn honks]

136
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:18,010
[stirring music continues]

137
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:25,101
[music turns tense]

138
00:12:29,623 --> 00:12:33,085
[gunshots in distance]

139
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:38,090
[whispers] Datu Rahman?

140
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:40,426
[tires screeching]

141
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:51,687
Father, let's go!

142
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:14,502
Datu Rahman?

143
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:21,425
[tense music continues]

144
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,029
- Jalil!
- [gasps]

145
00:13:45,366 --> 00:13:47,076
Father, let's go!

146
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:48,536
[Datu Rahman grunts]

147
00:13:57,753 --> 00:14:00,256
- [Datu Rahman groans]
- Father, come on. [grunts]

148
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:03,050
Just a little bit more.
Just a little bit more.

149
00:14:03,842 --> 00:14:05,010
[Jalil grunts]

150
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:07,513
- Father.
- [Datu Rahman exhales heavily]

151
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,850
[Jalil breathing heavily]

152
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,603
Don't move!

153
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:17,106
[stirring music playing]

154
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:29,535
Give me back Datu Rahman.

155
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:32,413
Usman, please…

156
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:34,540
Let us go!

157
00:14:34,623 --> 00:14:36,292
[Jalil breathes heavily]

158
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,711
[Jalil] We don't have to kill each other.

159
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,338
Usman…

160
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,674
I know you're a good cop!

161
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:47,261
You know me?

162
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,263
Who are you?!

163
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:52,057
[Jalil] We don't
have to get to this point.

164
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:56,729
What do you want from Datu Rahman?!

165
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,732
Answer me!

166
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:03,485
[stirring music continues]

167
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:25,883
‪[sniffs]

168
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:32,473
Major…

169
00:15:33,515 --> 00:15:34,767
Allan Espina?

170
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:39,438
[stirring music continues]

171
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,107
I'm not Espina.

172
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:44,860
I am Jalil.

173
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:46,946
Jalil Abubakar.

174
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:51,825
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

175
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:55,329
[stirring music continues]

176
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:05,881
[in English] Call Felix.

177
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:08,425
[line ringing]

178
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:09,843
[phone ringing]

179
00:16:10,511 --> 00:16:11,720
Madam!

180
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:13,305
Where are you?

181
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,224
I'm almost there.

182
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:17,518
Okay, hurry up.

183
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:19,353
Um…

184
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:20,980
Lara…

185
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:24,316
I'm glad you finally asked for my help.

186
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:27,236
[in English] God, Felix, shut up! Shut up!

187
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:28,612
[in English] I need you to focus!

188
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:30,906
Hurry up! We can't let Datu Rahman escape!

189
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:33,659
[tense music playing]

190
00:16:39,623 --> 00:16:40,874
Jalil Abubakar…

191
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:44,003
- Son of…
- I am.

192
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:47,756
I'm his son, so please, let us escape.

193
00:16:48,757 --> 00:16:52,386
He's safer if he's with me, Usman.

194
00:16:54,513 --> 00:16:55,931
I can't let you.

195
00:16:56,598 --> 00:16:59,309
- Give back Datu Rahman!
- You know that he's innocent.

196
00:17:02,646 --> 00:17:06,984
Usman, the video going around
has been edited to frame him up.

197
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:11,196
That's why you hid him, right?
To protect him?

198
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,906
[tense dramatic music continues]

199
00:17:13,615 --> 00:17:16,702
Because you knew those goons
could abduct him again.

200
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:20,289
You don't even trust
your own comrades in NLEA.

201
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:23,459
Am I right?

202
00:17:23,959 --> 00:17:28,797
[suspenseful music playing]

203
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:30,507
Hand over Datu Rahman to me.

204
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:32,217
- Usman--
- No, Father.

205
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:33,969
Usman, my father is just being framed up.

206
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:38,182
He's just being blamed,

207
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:41,310
because they know it's so easy
to put the blame on us.

208
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:46,315
Usman, you know what I mean.

209
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:50,194
Because you're also a Muslim.

210
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:52,571
[tense dramatic music continues]

211
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,656
You should understand.

212
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:02,498
Usman, you will let me do
my duty as a son.

213
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,875
I have to protect my father.

214
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:11,507
My father's in danger as long
as I haven't taken him into hiding.

215
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,760
Please.

216
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:19,640
[tense dramatic music continues]

217
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:24,520
Usman…

218
00:18:44,998 --> 00:18:47,709
[tense music continues]

219
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:52,256
[In Tausug] Thank you.

220
00:18:53,173 --> 00:18:54,758
- [in Tausug] Thank you.
- [in Tausug] Thank you.

221
00:18:57,177 --> 00:18:59,805
[sinister music playing]

222
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:26,498
[sinister music continues]

223
00:19:26,582 --> 00:19:28,375
[Jalil] My father's just being blamed,

224
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:31,503
because they know it's so easy
to put the blame on us.

225
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:36,508
Usman, you know what I mean.

226
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:40,304
Because you're also a Muslim.

227
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:43,515
[suspenseful music playing]

228
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:47,686
Usman, you will let me do
my duty as a son.

229
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:50,022
I have to protect my father.

230
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:56,695
My father's in danger as long
as I haven't taken him into hiding.

231
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:00,449
[Usman] <i>Did I do the right thing?</i>

232
00:20:01,408 --> 00:20:03,202
<i>What will I say to Marcus?</i>

233
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:05,579
[suspenseful music continues]

234
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,714
We'll stay here for now, Father.

235
00:20:15,797 --> 00:20:18,008
Let's make sure
that nobody's following us first.

236
00:20:20,093 --> 00:20:21,595
How have you been?

237
00:20:23,263 --> 00:20:24,473
Were you hurt?

238
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:27,809
I'm fine, son. Don't worry about me.

239
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:28,977
You're safe now, Father.

240
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:31,855
You're finally safe.

241
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:33,857
How did you find me?

242
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:35,442
Why do you look like that?

243
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:37,611
What happened?

244
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:41,782
And why did the officer
call you Major Allan Espina?

245
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:45,619
Father, I had to get inside NLEA.

246
00:20:46,870 --> 00:20:49,790
I put on a different identity to find you…

247
00:20:49,873 --> 00:20:50,791
[Datu Rahman exhales]

248
00:20:50,874 --> 00:20:54,253
…and to find out who was
responsible for all of this.

249
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:58,298
What you're doing is dangerous, son.

250
00:20:58,382 --> 00:21:00,592
- [inhales]
- Let's just get out of here.

251
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,720
Let's go far away, with Jamilah.

252
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:06,098
I don't want either of you
to get harmed because of me.

253
00:21:06,181 --> 00:21:07,724
No, Father.

254
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:10,686
We will return to the island.

255
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:12,479
[pensive music playing]

256
00:21:12,562 --> 00:21:14,690
I will clear your name.

257
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:18,819
We will return to living peacefully.

258
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:22,948
It's because of that island that…

259
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:25,826
I received my name…

260
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,955
I developed my identity…

261
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,376
And most importantly…

262
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:38,088
I got to have a family.

263
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,509
[pensive music continues]

264
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:50,142
[young Jalil sniffling]

265
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:52,728
Please don't leave me.

266
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:57,858
- [young Jalil crying]
- My child…

267
00:21:57,941 --> 00:22:01,403
I promise you that… I won't leave you.

268
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:02,946
[young Jalil sobbing]

269
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:10,287
[young Jalil crying]

270
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:16,501
Jalil. My son.

271
00:22:18,295 --> 00:22:19,463
Father.

272
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:24,343
- Father!
- [young Datu Rahman chuckling]

273
00:22:25,969 --> 00:22:28,096
Thank Allah! I'm glad
you've returned safely.

274
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:29,681
- How have you been?
- Jalil!

275
00:22:30,474 --> 00:22:31,641
[Jalil] Jamilah!

276
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:34,936
- [Jalil] Jamilah.
- [Jamilah] Jalil!

277
00:22:35,771 --> 00:22:37,064
[Jamilah] What took you so long
to come back?

278
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:38,398
[man 1] Jalil!

279
00:22:38,482 --> 00:22:39,441
[man 2] Peace be upon you!

280
00:22:41,151 --> 00:22:44,529
I won't turn my back
on our island, Father.

281
00:22:45,655 --> 00:22:49,409
- I won't abandon our people there.
- [spiritual music playing]

282
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:52,913
Their lives were also ruined, Father.

283
00:22:52,996 --> 00:22:54,081
[Jalil breathes heavily]

284
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:56,083
So I'm not going to stop

285
00:22:56,166 --> 00:22:58,460
until I find out

286
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:01,129
who did this to us.

287
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:03,465
[foreboding music playing]

288
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:06,218
We will get back all the secrets
that they have kept from us.

289
00:23:07,928 --> 00:23:08,970
Everything!

290
00:23:12,849 --> 00:23:13,975
[in Arabic] God willing.

291
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:17,771
[spiritual music playing]

292
00:23:17,854 --> 00:23:19,397
[Datu Rahman, in Arabic]
<i>God has willed it.</i>

293
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:31,660
[tense music playing]

294
00:23:33,787 --> 00:23:35,539
[Marcus] <i>Ma, I found Harold.</i>

295
00:23:35,622 --> 00:23:37,874
[Marcus] I don't know how
to tell his grandmother

296
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:40,877
that her grandson is alive,
but I can't hand him back to her yet.

297
00:23:41,545 --> 00:23:43,130
[Manuel] <i>Don't worry.</i>

298
00:23:43,213 --> 00:23:47,509
I will make sure that

299
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:51,054
everything that we started
wouldn't go to waste.

300
00:23:51,555 --> 00:23:54,724
[Jamilah] Where is he? Where's Jalil?

301
00:23:58,145 --> 00:23:59,312
- [Jamilah] Father?
- [Norhana sobs]

302
00:24:01,356 --> 00:24:04,359
[Lara] Find Datu Rahman.
I don't care how you'll do it.

303
00:24:04,442 --> 00:24:06,319
[Lara] <i>You want to make me happy,</i>
<i>don't you?</i>

304
00:24:06,403 --> 00:24:07,362
I'll take care of it.

305
00:24:07,445 --> 00:24:11,825
[Jalil] Please tell me, Father.
What do they want from you?

306
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:15,704
[Datu Rahman] <i>You're already dead,</i>
<i>so who is doing this?</i>

307
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:17,581
Was Datu Rahman telling the truth?

308
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:19,332
Were they really not the ones
who smuggled those arms?

309
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:22,377
[Marcus] <i>Are their protectors from NLEA?</i>

310
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:24,546
[Azuelo] <i>Agent Reyes!</i>
